name: AsaMetadataRegistry

methods.name: arc89_create_metadata

args.name: asset_id
args.desc: The Asset ID to create the Asset Metadata for

args.name: reversible_flags
args.desc: The Reversible Flags. WARNING: LSB and 1 can by set only at creation time

args.name: irreversible_flags
args.desc: The Irreversible Flags. WARNING: if the MSB is True the Asset Metadata is IMMUTABLE

args.name: metadata_size
args.desc: The Metadata byte size to be created

args.name: payload
args.desc: The Metadata payload (without Header). WARNING: Payload larger than args capacity must be provided with arc89_extra_payload calls in the Group

args.name: mbr_delta_payment
args.desc: Payment of the MBR Delta amount (microALGO) for the Asset Metadata Box creation

returns.desc: MBR Delta: tuple of (sign enum, amount in microALGO)

methods.desc: Create Asset Metadata for an existing ASA, restricted to the ASA Manager Address.

events.name: Arc89MetadataUpdated
events.desc: Event emitted when Asset Metadata is created or updated

methods.name: arc89_replace_metadata

args.name: asset_id
args.desc: The Asset ID to replace the Asset Metadata for

args.name: metadata_size
args.desc: The new Metadata byte size, must be less than or equal to the existing

args.name: payload
args.desc: The Metadata payload (without Header). WARNING: Payload larger than args capacity must be provided with arc89_extra_payload calls in the Group

returns.desc: MBR Delta: tuple of (sign enum, amount in microALGO)

methods.desc:
Replace mutable Metadata with a smaller or equal size payload for an existing ASA,
restricted to the ASA Manager Address.

events.name: Arc89MetadataUpdated
events.desc: Event emitted when Asset Metadata is created or updated

methods.name: arc89_replace_metadata_larger

args.name: asset_id
args.desc: The Asset ID to replace the Asset Metadata for

args.name: metadata_size
args.desc: The new Metadata byte size, must be larger than the existing

args.name: payload
args.desc: The Metadata payload (without Header). WARNING: Payload larger than args capacity must be provided with arc89_extra_payload calls in the Group

args.name: mbr_delta_payment
args.desc: Payment of the MBR Delta amount (microALGO) for the larger Asset Metadata Box replace

returns.desc: MBR Delta: tuple of (sign enum, amount in microALGO)

methods.desc:
Replace mutable Metadata with a larger size payload for an existing ASA,
restricted to the ASA Manager Address.

events.name: Arc89MetadataUpdated
events.desc: Event emitted when Asset Metadata is created or updated

args.name: asset_id
args.desc: The Asset ID to replace the Asset Metadata slice for

args.name: offset

args.name: payload

Replace a slice of the Asset Metadata for an ASA with a payload of the same size,
restricted to the ASA Manager Address.

methods.name: arc89_get_metadata_registry_parameters

returns.desc: Tuple of (HEADER_SIZE, MAX_METADATA_SIZE, SHORT_METADATA_SIZE, PAGE_SIZE, FIRST_PAYLOAD_MAX_SIZE, EXTRA_PAYLOAD_MAX_SIZE, REPLACE_PAYLOAD_MAX_SIZE, FLAT_MBR, BYTE_MBR)

methods.desc: Return the ASA Metadata Registry parameters.

methods.name: arc89_get_metadata_mbr_delta

args.name: asset_id
args.desc: The Asset ID to calculate the Asset Metadata MBR Delta for

args.name: new_metadata_size
args.desc: The new Asset Metadata byte size

returns.desc: MBR Delta: tuple of (sign enum, amount in microALGO)

methods.desc:
Return the Asset Metadata Box MBR Delta for an ASA, given a new Asset Metadata byte size.
If the Asset Metadata Box does not exist, the creation MBR Delta is returned.

args.name: asset_id
args.desc: The Asset ID to check the ASA and Asset Metadata existence for

returns.desc: Tuple of (ASA exists, Asset Metadata exists)

methods.desc: Checks whether the specified ASA exists and whether its associated Asset Metadata is available.
